.TH "vmw_query_bo_switch_prepare" 9 "vmw_query_bo_switch_prepare" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_query_bo_switch_prepare \- Prepare to switch pinned buffer for queries.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_query_bo_switch_prepare
.BI "(struct vmw_private *dev_priv "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_buffer_object *new_query_bo "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_sw_context *sw_context "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
The device private structure.
.IP "new_query_bo" 12
The new buffer holding query results.
.IP "sw_context" 12
The software context used for this command submission.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks whether \fInew_query_bo\fP is suitable for holding query
results, and if another buffer currently is pinned for query results. If so,
the function prepares the state of \fIsw_context\fP for switching pinned buffers
after successful submission of the current command batch.
